{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nOnce rebar owns the OIDC provider and the domain-wide SSO stack (story ample-famous-cockatiel), rebar's infra docs must describe the ownership, dependencies, and operations (secret rotation, incident revoke) so they live in rebar's tree, not snap's dead repo.\n\n## What\n- Update `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md`: add a subsection noting rebar now OWNS the GitHub OIDC provider (previously assumed \"already exists in the account\"), the `*.solutions.navateam.com` wildcard cert, and the `auth_host` domain-wide SSO stack — pointing at the ADR and the SSO runbook.\n- Fix the stale comment in `infra/terraform/iam.tf` that said the OIDC provider \"already exists in the account\" now that rebar creates/owns it (already applied in the terraform story's commit).\n- Add an ADR under `docs/adr/` recording the snap→rebar re-homing decision: adopt-vs-teardown, import-not-recreate, name-preservation tradeoff, cookie-secret idiom change, and the state migration.\n- Add an SSO operations runbook under `infra/runbooks/sso-auth-host.md` adapted from snap's `auth/RUNBOOK.md`, covering: the auth-host architecture, the `/auth-solutions/*` secrets, cookie-signing-key rotation (SSM overwrite + Lambda `-replace`), Google-`client_secret` rotation, and the incident revoke lever. It also notes how a future rebar subdomain would opt into the SSO, but that section is descriptive prose — it does not gate this ticket.\n\n## Scope\nDocumentation only (the terraform + module code land in story ample-famous-cockatiel). Four artifacts: the gerrit-aws-setup.md subsection, the iam.tf comment, the ADR, and the SSO runbook.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/gerrit-aws-setup.md` documents rebar's ownership of the OIDC provider + the wildcard cert + the auth_host SSO stack, linking the ADR + runbook.\n- [ ] `infra/terraform/iam.tf`'s OIDC comment no longer claims the provider is externally owned.\n- [ ] An ADR under `docs/adr/` records the re-homing decision and its tradeoffs (adopt-vs-teardown, import-not-recreate, name preservation, state migration).\n- [ ] An `infra/runbooks/sso-auth-host.md` runbook covers the auth-host architecture, the `/auth-solutions/*` secrets, cookie-key + Google-secret rotation, and the incident revoke lever."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784049326986102001,"uuid":"3809125c-44bd-4d58-a490-e47b2d48a0b1"}